var_description: the amount of time using a breathing machine
the intensity level of a breathing machine from zero to high
insertion of tube through mouth or nose down trachae to support breathing
sudden blockage in the pulmonary arteries
breathing pressure from zero to high
high concentration of oxygen in the gas mixture
pulmonary venous oxygen saturation aka oxygen content of blood returning to right ventricle
arterial CO2 aka marker of sufficient alveolar ventilation
total peripheral resistance = mean arterial pressure divided by cardiac output
left ventricle of heart no longer pumps enough blood around the body
abnormally low levels of extracellular fluids in the body
left ventricular end-diastolic volume aka the amount of blood in the left ventricular before the heart contracts
volume of blood pumped out of left ventricle of heart during cardiac contraction
pulmonary capillary wedge pressure aka estimate of LVEDVOLUME
central venous pressure aka right ventricular end-diastolic pressure which parallels left ventricular end-diastolic pressure with normal left ventricular function
cardiac output = stroke volume x heart rate
heart rate blood pressure from low to high
Heart rate displayed on EKG monitor from low to high
